{\pard\qc\f0\fs22\sb0\sa0\sl260\slmult0 Tuba City Fairgrounds Rodeo Arena  Tuba City  AZ\par}
{\pard\qc\f0\fs22\i\sb0\sa0\sl260\slmult0 Youth Camp\i0\par}
{\pard\qj\f0\fs22\sb40\sa0\sl260\slmult0 Song of the Horse Youth Camp 2026 is a free three-day event scheduled for June 4 through 6, 2026 at Tuba City Fairgrounds Rodeo Arena in Tuba City, Arizona. The flyer lists activities including Native Traditional Horse Day, Horse Songs and Stories, Horsemanship Presentations, Arena Riding Sessions, Equine Make-Over, Equine Facilitated Learning, Evening Arena Sessions, and an Obstacle Course Challenge across the three days. The camp is sponsored by the University of Arizona Cooperative Extension Tribal Extension Programs and the University of Colorado Boulder Ethnic Studies program, among other organizations listed on the flyer. Twenty riding spots are listed as available with unlimited non-riding spots for youth and adults. Limited horses will be available for participants without a horse. Boarding stalls will be available. T-shirts, prizes, and awards are listed for participants at no cost. Contact Grey Farrell at 928-614-8403 or GFarrell@cals.arizona.edu for registration and information.\par}
{\pard\qc\f0\fs18\i\sb0\sa80\sl220\slmult0 928-614-8403  |  GFarrell@cals.arizona.edu\i0\par}
